# TradeFrame — Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** March 18, 2026
**Developer:** Twelve52 (briansolly@gmail.com)

---

## Information We Collect

### Business Information
Company name, phone, and email entered in Settings. Stored locally and used only to populate your PDF reports, estimates, and invoices.

### Client Information
Names, addresses, phone numbers, and emails of your clients. Entered by you and stored locally to manage client relationships.

### Job & Financial Data
Job details, estimates, invoices, payments, milestones, and notes you create. All entered by you and stored locally on your device.

### Signatures
Customer signatures captured on-screen or photographed are stored with the associated estimate or report on your device.

### Photos & Camera
Photos taken through TradeFrame are stored within the app's local data store. Photos are never uploaded to our servers.

### Location (GPS)
With your permission, GPS coordinates are captured at the moment of photo capture and embedded in photo metadata. Location is not tracked continuously. Deny access and the app works normally — photos just won't include GPS data.

### Microphone / Voice Notes
With your permission, on-device speech recognition transcribes voice notes. Audio is processed locally using Apple's Speech framework and is never transmitted externally. No audio recordings are stored — only the text transcription.

### Calendar
With your permission, TradeFrame reads and writes events to your Apple Calendar to sync job schedules. We do not access calendars beyond job event management.

---

## Data Storage

### Local Storage
All data is stored locally on your device using Apple's Core Data framework. We do not operate servers and do not transmit your data to any server we control.

### iCloud Sync (CloudKit)
If signed into iCloud, TradeFrame syncs data across your iOS devices via Apple's CloudKit. Your data is stored in your personal iCloud account, managed and encrypted by Apple. We do not have access to your iCloud data.

### Photo Storage
Photos are stored in the app's local data directory (not your Photo Library) and synced via CloudKit if iCloud is enabled. We never upload or process your photos on any external server.

---

## How We Use Your Data

### App Functionality Only
Your data is used solely to operate the app: displaying business info on PDFs, organizing clients and jobs, GPS-stamping photos, transcribing voice notes, syncing via iCloud, scheduling notifications, and creating calendar events.

---

## Advertising

### Google AdMob
The free tier of TradeFrame displays banner advertisements provided by Google AdMob. AdMob may collect the following data for advertising purposes:

- **Device identifiers** (IDFA, when you consent via the App Tracking Transparency prompt)
- **IP address** (used for approximate geolocation and fraud prevention)
- **General device information** (device model, OS version, screen size)
- **Ad interaction data** (impressions, clicks)

This data is collected and processed by Google according to Google's Privacy Policy (https://policies.google.com/privacy).

### App Tracking Transparency
On first launch, TradeFrame will ask your permission before allowing AdMob to track your activity across other companies' apps and websites. If you decline, ads will still be shown but will not be personalized.

### Ad-Free Experience
Subscribing to TradeFrame Pro removes all advertisements and stops AdMob data collection entirely. If your subscription lapses, ads and associated data collection resume.

